1. Open power shell run as admin 
2. wsl --install (first time only)
3. WSL integration on the docker 
4. Then check the docker version on the wsl
5. curl -sSLO https://raw.githubusercontent.com/hyperledger/fabric/main/scripts/install-fabric.sh
6. chmod +x install-fabric.sh
7. Inside the ubuntu terminal
8. docker run -d -p 8080:80 nginx
9. Open this link on the browser to check if nginix is working (http://localhost:8080)
10. docker ps
11. Open the docker app go to container you’ll see container is created for nginx
12. Click on nginx -> log
13. docker pull hyperledger/fabric-ca
14. docker run -d --name ca.example.com -p 7054:7054 hyperledger/fabric-ca fabric-ca-server start -b admin:adminpw
15. Shows the logs of the hyper ledger
